steve-b@access.digex.net (Steve Brinich) writes:

> > Has anyone given thought to the idea of allowing some "slop" in the
> >crypt-decrypt process?  What I mean is, for some kinds of text, who cares if
> >1 in 20 or 30 characters is wrong in the decrypted version?

Check out Dave August's piece in Cryptologia from three or four years
ago. (Sorry, I don't have the exact reference.) He suggests squooshing
out vowels or randomly making a few errors. 

